WEBVTT

00:01.902 --> 00:03.203
<i>PREVIOUSLY ON "THE HAVES</i>
<i>AND THE HAVE NOTS"...</i>

00:03.203 --> 00:04.404
WHY DIDN'T YOU JUST
SAY SOMETHING?

00:04.404 --> 00:06.006
WE'RE JUDGES. YOU'RE A LAWYER.
MAKE SOMETHING HAPPEN.

00:06.006 --> 00:07.407
AND THIS IS
WHERE THE CAR IS?

00:07.407 --> 00:08.842
YOU ARE A CRAZY ‐‐
SAY IT!

00:08.842 --> 00:10.511
AND I WILL
LAY YOUR ASS OUT!

00:10.511 --> 00:11.678
JEFFERY?
YEAH?

00:11.678 --> 00:13.714
DO YOU KNOW WHERE I COULD,
UH, BUY A GUN?

00:13.714 --> 00:15.081
DON'T TOUCH HIM.

00:15.081 --> 00:16.416
THEY WANT ME
TO TAKE HIM OFF IT.

00:16.416 --> 00:17.417
I CAN'T DO THIS.

00:17.417 --> 00:19.485
[ SOBBING ]

00:21.321 --> 00:23.557
[ Crying ] DON'T TOUCH ME!

00:23.557 --> 00:25.526
HEY, HEY.
THIS IS YOUR FAULT!

00:25.526 --> 00:26.593
WHAT THE HELL ARE YOU DOING
IN MY OFFICE?

00:26.593 --> 00:27.694
I NEED YOU
TO HELP MY BROTHER.

00:27.694 --> 00:30.363
CAN'T HELP YOU.

00:35.135 --> 00:37.437
HANNA? HANNA?

00:37.437 --> 00:38.605
YES?

00:38.605 --> 00:41.041
YOU WERE ABOUT TO TELL ME
WHO YOU THINK DID THIS.

00:41.041 --> 00:43.544
YEAH, I...

00:43.544 --> 00:46.547
I'M NOT SURE.

00:46.547 --> 00:49.415
BUT YOU HAVE
SOME SORT OF IDEA?

00:49.415 --> 00:51.718
YEAH. YES.

00:51.718 --> 00:53.486
WHO?

00:53.486 --> 00:57.658
I DON'T WANT TO GET ANYBODY
IN TROUBLE IF I'M WRONG.

00:57.658 --> 01:00.400
ONLY WAY TO KNOW IF YOU'RE WRONG
IS IF YOU LET ME INVESTIGATE IT.

01:00.400 --> 01:02.769
NO.

01:02.769 --> 01:05.739
I THINK I NEED TO BE SURE.

01:05.739 --> 01:07.273
LET ME HELP YOU BE SURE.

01:07.273 --> 01:08.775
NO.

01:08.775 --> 01:10.143
THIS IS ALL OVER THE NEWS,

01:10.143 --> 01:12.112
AND I DON'T WANT TO RUIN
SOMEBODY'S LIFE IF I'M WRONG.

01:12.112 --> 01:13.914
WILL YOU FILL ME IN
AT ALL?

01:13.914 --> 01:16.517
NOT YET.

01:16.517 --> 01:18.952
OKAY.

01:18.952 --> 01:20.286
[ SIGHS ] DETECTIVE...

01:20.286 --> 01:21.755
BYRON.

01:21.755 --> 01:25.125
BYRON, I CAN'T ‐‐
I CAN'T EVEN THINK STRAIGHT.

01:25.125 --> 01:27.861
I'M SORRY.
I KNOW.

01:27.861 --> 01:29.362
I KNOW
THIS MUST BE HARD.

01:29.362 --> 01:32.365
YOU HAVE NO IDEA.

01:32.365 --> 01:33.934
YOUR ONLY CHILD?

01:33.934 --> 01:35.536
I HAVE TWO.

01:35.536 --> 01:38.171
MY ONLY BOY.
HMM.

01:38.171 --> 01:40.140
GOOD KID?

01:40.140 --> 01:43.343
THE BEST.

01:43.343 --> 01:45.145
I'M SORRY.

01:45.145 --> 01:46.947
NEVER BEEN AWAY FROM ME
IN HIS LIFE.

01:46.947 --> 01:47.981
MM.

01:47.981 --> 01:50.283
SOUNDS LIKE
ME AND MY MOTHER.

01:50.283 --> 01:51.985
YOU'RE CLOSE?

01:51.985 --> 01:54.154
TILL SHE DIED.

01:54.154 --> 01:56.356
I'M SORRY.

01:56.356 --> 01:58.358
NO, DON'T BE.

01:58.358 --> 02:00.226
I TELL YOU,
THERE IS NOTHING

02:00.226 --> 02:02.569
LIKE THE LOVE OF A SON
TO HIS MOTHER.

02:02.569 --> 02:04.370
[ CHUCKLES ]

02:04.370 --> 02:05.438
YEAH.

02:05.438 --> 02:08.108
I DON'T KNOW IF GIRLS
REALLY HAVE THAT BOND.

02:08.108 --> 02:10.176
SOMETIMES THEY DO.

02:10.176 --> 02:11.545
BUT BOYS AND THEIR MAMAS...

02:11.545 --> 02:12.913
HMM. [ CHUCKLES ]

02:12.913 --> 02:13.947
SOMETIMES.

02:13.947 --> 02:16.550
ME AND MY MOTHER
WERE BEST FRIENDS.

02:16.550 --> 02:19.919
THAT'S ME AND BENNY.

02:19.919 --> 02:23.256
I WISH THERE WAS MORE
I COULD DO.

02:23.256 --> 02:25.792
THE ONLY THING
I CAN THINK ABOUT RIGHT NOW

02:25.792 --> 02:27.127
IS HIM GETTING BETTER.

02:27.127 --> 02:29.395
I UNDERSTAND THAT.

02:29.395 --> 02:30.564
DO YOU?

02:30.564 --> 02:32.933
YES, YES, YES.

02:32.933 --> 02:35.068
THIS CAN ALL WAIT.

02:35.068 --> 02:36.803
THANK YOU.

02:36.803 --> 02:39.740
SURE.

02:39.740 --> 02:42.008
MS. YOUNG?

02:42.008 --> 02:43.343
YES?

02:43.343 --> 02:45.411
WHEN'S THE LAST TIME
YOU'VE EATEN SOMETHING?

02:45.411 --> 02:46.647
OH. [ CHUCKLES ]

02:46.647 --> 02:48.715
NOW, IF YOU HAVE TO THINK ABOUT
IT, IT'S BEEN A WHILE.

02:48.715 --> 02:51.484
I'M NOT HUNGRY.

02:51.484 --> 02:53.419
YOU SHOULD EAT SOMETHING.
I CAN'T.

02:53.419 --> 02:55.288
CAN'T SURVIVE ON COFFEE
AND DOUGHNUTS, EITHER.

02:55.288 --> 02:57.090
TRUST ME. I KNOW.

02:57.090 --> 02:58.258
I'M FINE.

02:58.258 --> 03:03.436
IF YOU'RE GONNA KEEP
YOUR STRENGTH UP FOR HIM,

03:03.436 --> 03:05.438
YOU HAD BETTER
EAT SOMETHING.

03:05.438 --> 03:07.641
I WILL.

03:07.641 --> 03:09.776
YOU WANT TO GO DOWN
TO THE CAFETERIA?

03:09.776 --> 03:11.044
OH, NO.

03:11.044 --> 03:13.880
I'LL GRAB SOMETHING
FROM HOME.

03:13.880 --> 03:18.284
I'M GONNA GO TRY TO GRAB
A COUPLE OF HOURS OF SLEEP

03:18.284 --> 03:20.386
AND THEN COME BACK HERE.

03:20.386 --> 03:22.388
THANK YOU
FOR COMING TO SEE ME.

03:22.388 --> 03:23.924
SURE.

03:23.924 --> 03:25.491
CAN I GIVE YOU A RIDE?

03:25.491 --> 03:27.961
NO, THANK YOU.
I DON'T NEED A RIDE.

03:27.961 --> 03:29.863
OH.
LOOKS LIKE RAIN OUT THERE.

03:29.863 --> 03:31.765
SURE YOU WON'T TAKE
THIS RIDE?

03:31.765 --> 03:32.966
I KNOW YOU'RE TIRED.

03:32.966 --> 03:35.301
BUT I DON'T KNOW YOU.

03:35.301 --> 03:37.904
YOU KNOW I'M AN OFFICER.

03:37.904 --> 03:40.874
LET ME SEE YOUR BADGE AGAIN.

03:40.874 --> 03:43.043
HARD TO TRUST, RIGHT?

03:44.878 --> 03:46.079
NO OFFENSE.

03:46.079 --> 03:47.748
NO, I UNDERSTAND.

03:47.748 --> 03:50.150
I GREW UP AROUND HERE, TOO.

03:50.150 --> 03:52.886
NOW,
YOU'LL TAKE THIS RIDE?

03:52.886 --> 03:54.955
I AM KIND OF TIRED.

03:54.955 --> 03:57.223
ALL RIGHT, THANK YOU.

03:57.223 --> 03:59.259
NO PROBLEM.

