04:12.779 --> 04:14.815
[ CRICKETS CHIRPING ]

04:18.384 --> 04:21.988
YEAH, KEEP ME POSTED.

04:21.988 --> 04:24.057
OH, YOU THINK?

04:24.057 --> 04:25.526
WELL, I ‐‐

04:25.526 --> 04:27.393
DAD?
WYATT.

04:27.393 --> 04:29.530
YEAH. THANKS. THANKS.

04:29.530 --> 04:30.631
[ CELLPHONE BEEPS ]

04:30.631 --> 04:32.132
I WANTED
TO TALK TO YOU.

04:32.132 --> 04:34.000
COME ON IN.

04:34.000 --> 04:35.669
HAVE A SEAT.

04:35.669 --> 04:38.137
WHAT'S ON YOUR MIND?

04:38.137 --> 04:39.673
HOW'S EVERYTHING GOING?

04:39.673 --> 04:42.075
HOW'S IT GOING?

04:42.075 --> 04:44.711
HOW'S WHAT GOING?

04:44.711 --> 04:46.580
EVERYTHING.

04:46.580 --> 04:48.481
OH.

04:48.481 --> 04:51.652
BY "EVERYTHING," YOU MEAN
MY COVER‐UP FOR YOU.

04:51.652 --> 04:53.453
IS THAT RIGHT?

04:55.021 --> 04:56.723
SORRY, DAD.

04:56.723 --> 04:57.991
DON'T WORRY ABOUT IT.

04:57.991 --> 05:00.060
DAVID AND I HAVE A PLAN
IN PLACE.

05:00.060 --> 05:01.067
OKAY, WHAT IS IT?

05:01.067 --> 05:03.036
I'M NOT GONNA TELL YOU THAT,
WYATT.

05:03.036 --> 05:06.573
WE'RE WATCHING THE WHOLE THING
VERY, VERY CLOSELY.

05:06.573 --> 05:09.209
YOU REALIZE HOW BAD THIS IS,
RIGHT?

05:09.209 --> 05:11.244
YEAH.

05:11.244 --> 05:14.180
IT'S ON THE NEWS
EVERY SINGLE DAY.

05:14.180 --> 05:16.049
YES, IT IS.

05:16.049 --> 05:17.784
EVERY DAY.

05:17.784 --> 05:19.553
WHAT THE HELL
WERE YOU THINKING?

05:19.553 --> 05:21.955
I WASN'T.

05:21.955 --> 05:24.791
THAT'S RIGHT.
YOU WEREN'T.

05:24.791 --> 05:27.594
DAD, I'M HAVING A REAL HARD TIME
WITH THIS.

05:27.594 --> 05:29.229
SO, WHAT ARE YOU TELLING ME,
SON?

05:29.229 --> 05:31.297
YOU'RE TELLING ME YOU WANT
TO GET HIGH AGAIN?

05:31.297 --> 05:34.267
DAD...

05:34.267 --> 05:36.302
I DON'T EVER WANT
TO GET HIGH AGAIN.

05:36.302 --> 05:38.138
REALLY?

05:38.138 --> 05:41.742
YEAH.

05:41.742 --> 05:44.044
WELL, THAT'S GOOD, WYATT.

05:44.044 --> 05:45.579
THAT'S A START.

05:45.579 --> 05:49.115
I'VE NEVER HEARD YOU
SAY THAT BEFORE.

05:49.115 --> 05:51.151
I MEAN IT, DAD.

05:51.151 --> 05:53.554
SO, YOU UNDERSTAND
THAT EVERYTHING YOU DO

05:53.554 --> 05:56.623
NOT ONLY AFFECTS YOU, BUT IT
AFFECTS THE ENTIRE FAMILY.

05:56.623 --> 05:57.924
YES, I SEE THAT.

05:57.924 --> 06:01.467
THAT'S ALL I'VE EVER WANTED
YOU TO SEE, SON.

06:01.467 --> 06:04.838
DAD...

06:04.838 --> 06:08.575
MAYBE I SHOULD
JUST CONFESS.

06:08.575 --> 06:11.011
IS THAT
WHAT YOU REALLY WANT?

06:12.846 --> 06:15.982
I DON'T KNOW.

06:15.982 --> 06:19.452
THINK ABOUT IT, WYATT.

06:19.452 --> 06:21.655
WE ALL KNOW.

06:21.655 --> 06:23.957
I KNOW.
YOUR MOTHER KNOWS.

06:23.957 --> 06:25.659
THE HARRINGTONS KNOW.

06:25.659 --> 06:29.095
YOU NEED TO KEEP THIS WHOLE
THING A SECRET, SON,

06:29.095 --> 06:31.932
NOT ONLY FOR YOU,
BUT FOR EVERYONE INVOLVED.

06:31.932 --> 06:33.667
DO YOU SEE THAT?
YEAH, DAD.

06:33.667 --> 06:35.401
THE LITTLE GIRL?

06:35.401 --> 06:37.671
THE LITTLE GIRL IS DEAD.

06:37.671 --> 06:41.542
NOTHING YOU COULD DO
TO CHANGE THAT, SON.

06:41.542 --> 06:45.078
YOU CONFESS,
YOU TURN YOURSELF IN,

06:45.078 --> 06:47.147
WHAT DOES IT CHANGE?

06:47.147 --> 06:48.549
HANNA'S SON.

06:48.549 --> 06:50.851
YOU LET ME WORRY
ABOUT HANNA'S SON,

06:50.851 --> 06:53.019
AND YOU LET ME WORRY
ABOUT HANNA.

06:53.019 --> 06:54.888
YES, BUT WHAT IF SHE SAYS
THAT IT'S ME?

06:54.888 --> 06:57.758
LET ME WORRY ABOUT HANNA.

06:57.758 --> 06:59.092
TRUST ME.

06:59.092 --> 07:00.934
I HAVE THIS UNDER CONTROL.

07:06.106 --> 07:08.174
OKAY.

07:08.174 --> 07:10.577
OKAY.

07:10.577 --> 07:14.881
SO, THEN, WHAT CAN I DO
TO SHOW THEM I'M SORRY?

07:17.183 --> 07:19.452
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

07:19.452 --> 07:21.487
YOU KEEP YOURSELF CLEAN,

07:21.487 --> 07:23.857
YOU KEEP YOUR HEAD
HELD UP HIGH,

07:23.857 --> 07:25.992
AND YOU STAY THE HELL
OUT OF TROUBLE.

07:25.992 --> 07:28.595
THAT'S HOW YOU SHOW EVERYONE
THAT YOU'RE SORRY.

07:28.595 --> 07:32.165
YOU UNDERSTAND?

07:32.165 --> 07:33.934
YEAH.

07:33.934 --> 07:35.736
GOOD.

07:35.736 --> 07:40.406
AND, WYATT,
WHEN YOU SEE HANNA,

07:40.406 --> 07:42.976
JUST BE YOURSELF.

07:42.976 --> 07:44.845
YOU GOT ME?

07:44.845 --> 07:46.780
YES.

07:46.780 --> 07:50.016
I LOVE YOU, SON.

07:50.016 --> 07:51.885
I LOVE YOU, TOO, DAD.

07:51.885 --> 07:55.837
I'LL ALWAYS PROTECT YOU
WITH EVERYTHING I'VE GOT.

07:58.324 --> 08:00.867
GO GET SOME SLEEP.

08:00.867 --> 08:03.069
GO ON.

08:45.512 --> 08:47.714
THANK YOU.

08:51.184 --> 08:53.019
THIS YOUR HOUSE?

08:53.019 --> 08:54.521
YEAH.

08:54.521 --> 08:56.022
NICE.

08:56.022 --> 08:58.792
THANKS.
I APPRECIATE IT.

09:00.901 --> 09:03.436
W‐WHERE ARE YOU GOING?

09:03.436 --> 09:07.040
I'M WALKING YOU
TO YOUR DOOR.

09:07.040 --> 09:09.375
NO, THAT'S ALL RIGHT.
I'M FINE.

09:09.375 --> 09:11.044
OKAY.

09:11.044 --> 09:12.112
SORRY.

09:12.112 --> 09:14.681
IT'S A HABIT, I GUESS.

09:14.681 --> 09:15.716
HABIT?

09:15.716 --> 09:17.117
YEAH.

09:17.117 --> 09:19.786
MY MOTHER USED TO LIVE IN
A NEIGHBORHOOD JUST LIKE THIS.

09:19.786 --> 09:23.323
I'D ALWAYS GO IN,
CHECK THE HOUSE FOR HER.

09:23.323 --> 09:25.258
WELL, MY HOUSE IS FINE.

09:25.258 --> 09:27.928
OKAY. I'M SORRY.

09:27.928 --> 09:32.132
YOU KNOW,
CAN I BE HONEST WITH YOU?

09:32.132 --> 09:34.901
PLEASE.

09:34.901 --> 09:38.438
THIS ISN'T EVEN
MY JURISDICTION.

09:38.438 --> 09:40.741
I SAW YOU ON THE NEWS,

09:40.741 --> 09:44.578
AND MY HEART WENT OUT
TO YOU AND YOUR SON,

09:44.578 --> 09:46.680
AND I'M JUST TRYING TO HELP.

09:46.680 --> 09:49.850
WELL,
I APPRECIATE THAT A LOT.

09:49.850 --> 09:51.084
THANK YOU.

09:51.084 --> 09:52.352
SURE.

09:52.352 --> 09:54.154
AND I HOPE HE MAKES IT.

09:54.154 --> 09:55.221
HE WILL.

09:55.221 --> 09:57.190
YES, HE WILL.

09:57.190 --> 09:59.392
GOOD NIGHT.

09:59.392 --> 10:01.602
GOOD NIGHT.

10:10.944 --> 10:12.245
[ CAR DOOR CLOSES ]

10:12.245 --> 10:14.180
[ ENGINE TURNS OVER ]

10:24.224 --> 10:27.694
WHO CUT MY GRASS?

10:30.597 --> 10:33.466
WHO CUT MY GRASS?

11:02.869 --> 11:04.771
SO, HER BROTHER GOT
IN AN ACCIDENT?

11:04.771 --> 11:06.239
YEAH.

11:06.239 --> 11:08.141
HOW IS HE?

11:08.141 --> 11:10.476
I DON'T KNOW.
SHE WENT TO GO SEE HIM.

11:10.476 --> 11:12.713
WOW.

11:12.713 --> 11:15.415
YOU DON'T UNDERSTAND.
CANDACE LOVES HER BROTHER.

11:15.415 --> 11:18.351
YEAH, I KNOW.
I MEAN, I GET IT.

11:18.351 --> 11:19.820
THIS IS SO SAD.

11:19.820 --> 11:21.087
I'M GONNA TRY AND CALL HER.

11:21.087 --> 11:22.322
NO, NO, NO.
DON'T CALL.

11:22.322 --> 11:24.124
SHE'S PROBABLY STILL
AT THE HOSPITAL.

11:24.124 --> 11:26.459
YEAH, YOU'RE RIGHT.

11:26.459 --> 11:28.494
WOW.

11:31.598 --> 11:35.368
AMANDA, THE OTHER DAY,
YOU SAID YOU WANTED A GUN.

11:35.368 --> 11:37.938
YEAH.

11:37.938 --> 11:39.940
BUT YOU NEVER SAID
WHY YOU WANTED IT.

11:39.940 --> 11:43.910
I'M GONNA KILL MY PARENTS.

11:43.910 --> 11:45.245
WHAT?

11:45.245 --> 11:46.947
YEAH.

11:46.947 --> 11:50.183
I'M GONNA WAIT
TILL THEY FALL ASLEEP,

11:50.183 --> 11:54.020
AND I'M GONNA GO INTO THE HOUSE
AND KILL THEM.

11:54.020 --> 11:57.123
AND WYATT, TOO.

11:57.123 --> 11:59.593
W‐W‐WHY WOULD YOU
WANT TO ‐‐

11:59.593 --> 12:02.235
WHY WOULD YOU
WANT TO DO THAT?

12:02.235 --> 12:05.572
IT'S GONNA BE FUN.

12:05.572 --> 12:08.108
AMANDA, I DON'T THINK
THAT'S A GOOD IDEA.

12:08.108 --> 12:10.443
WHY NOT?

12:10.443 --> 12:12.779
WHY NOT?

12:12.779 --> 12:14.948
UH, WELL...

12:14.948 --> 12:17.984
COME ON, MR. PSYCHOLOGIST
LIVING ON MY SOFA.

12:17.984 --> 12:18.985
OKAY.
THINK FAST.

12:18.985 --> 12:20.286
OKAY.
TALK ME OUT OF IT.

12:20.286 --> 12:22.756
OKAY. WELL ‐‐

12:22.756 --> 12:23.990
YOU'RE FAILING.

12:23.990 --> 12:25.726
I...

12:25.726 --> 12:27.594
ARE YOU ‐‐ ARE YOU ‐‐
ARE YOU ANGRY WITH THEM?

12:27.594 --> 12:29.996
YOU'RE GONNA HAVE TO DO
BETTER THAN THAT.

12:29.996 --> 12:32.265
WELL?

12:32.265 --> 12:34.701
[ LAUGHS ]

12:36.537 --> 12:38.805
LOOK AT YOUR FACE.

12:41.942 --> 12:43.644
I HAVE...

12:46.680 --> 12:49.883
JEFFERY,
I'M JUST KIDDING.

12:52.352 --> 12:53.954
OH.

12:53.954 --> 12:56.022
I AM.

12:56.022 --> 12:59.225
WE'RE TWO GIRLS
LIVING ALONE.

12:59.225 --> 13:00.834
WE NEED A GUN.

13:00.834 --> 13:02.603
DON'T YOU THINK?

13:02.603 --> 13:05.005
NO, THIS IS
A SAFE NEIGHBORHOOD.

13:05.005 --> 13:06.507
YOU DON'T NEED A GUN.

13:06.507 --> 13:10.243
MAYBE YOU'RE RIGHT.

13:10.243 --> 13:12.579
WILL YOU RELAX?

13:12.579 --> 13:15.481
I WAS JUST KIDDING
ABOUT MY PARENTS.

13:15.481 --> 13:17.383
GEEZ.

13:17.383 --> 13:20.621
I COULD NEVER DO
SOMETHING LIKE THAT.

13:23.724 --> 13:25.191
YEAH, OKAY.

13:25.191 --> 13:27.594
I MEAN, I KNOW YOU...

13:27.594 --> 13:29.696
I FIGURED
YOU WERE KIDDING.

13:29.696 --> 13:32.232
I AM.

13:32.232 --> 13:33.934
OKAY.

13:33.934 --> 13:35.636
GOOD.

13:35.636 --> 13:40.974
ALTHOUGH YOU MAY NEED A GUN
FOR YOUR PARENTS.

13:40.974 --> 13:43.309
OH, NO. DON'T ‐‐
DON'T EVEN PLAY THAT WAY.

13:43.309 --> 13:45.078
SORRY.

13:45.078 --> 13:46.647
MAYBE JUST YOUR MOTHER.

13:46.647 --> 13:48.481
STOP IT.
SHE'S A WITCH.

13:48.481 --> 13:49.482
SHE'S MY MOM.

13:49.482 --> 13:51.885
YEAH,
AND I'M SORRY FOR YOU.

13:51.885 --> 13:53.787
YOU TOLD ME ALL THE THINGS
SHE SAID

13:53.787 --> 13:55.522
WHEN YOU CAME OUT
AND TOLD HER.

13:55.522 --> 13:56.523
THAT'S JUST WRONG.

13:56.523 --> 13:58.158
I KNOW IT'S WRONG.

13:58.158 --> 14:00.233
WELL, HAVE YOU SEEN HER
SINCE THEN?

14:02.636 --> 14:04.938
YEAH. I SAW HER THE OTHER DAY
AT YOUR HOUSE.

14:04.938 --> 14:07.207
WHAT WERE YOU DOING THERE?

14:07.207 --> 14:09.375
TALKING TO WYATT.

14:09.375 --> 14:10.476
OH.

14:10.476 --> 14:12.546
HOW IS HE?

14:12.546 --> 14:14.781
HE'S FINE.

14:14.781 --> 14:16.116
HMM.

14:16.116 --> 14:18.685
WELL,
WHAT DID YOUR MOTHER SAY?

14:18.685 --> 14:21.922
SHE...

14:21.922 --> 14:25.225
SHE WANTED TO MEET
FOR LUNCH.

14:25.225 --> 14:27.528
CAN YOU BELIEVE THAT?
WOW. REALLY?

14:27.528 --> 14:29.996
YEAH.

14:29.996 --> 14:31.965
ARE YOU GONNA GO?

14:31.965 --> 14:33.867
YEAH.

14:33.867 --> 14:35.936
CASTRATION TIME.

14:35.936 --> 14:37.237
[ LAUGHS ]

14:37.237 --> 14:38.539
NOT FUNNY.

14:38.539 --> 14:39.940
[ SMACKS LIPS ]

14:39.940 --> 14:42.108
[ LAUGHING ]

14:54.788 --> 14:57.691
[ Woman over P. A. ]
<i>PAGING DR. BENDER.</i>

14:57.691 --> 15:00.466
<i>PAGING DR. BENDER, PLEASE.</i>

15:02.903 --> 15:05.839
VISITING HOURS
IS BETWEEN, UH...

15:05.839 --> 15:08.074
OH. IT'S YOU.

15:08.074 --> 15:10.644
GOODBYE.

15:10.644 --> 15:13.213
[ MONITOR BEEPING ]

15:24.024 --> 15:27.327
REMEMBER
WHEN WE WERE LITTLE

15:27.327 --> 15:32.432
AND YOU USED TO MAKE
THOSE BANANA SPLITS FOR US?

15:32.432 --> 15:35.468
THEY WERE SO GROSS.

15:35.468 --> 15:39.476
YOU USED TO PUT MUSTARD ON YOURS
AND TRIED TO MAKE ME EAT IT.

15:41.742 --> 15:45.579
I THOUGHT ABOUT THAT
THIS MORNING.

15:45.579 --> 15:48.615
THEN I STARTED THINKING ABOUT

15:48.615 --> 15:51.685
WHEN THAT BOY
WAS MESSING WITH ME.

15:51.685 --> 15:54.287
MILTON.

15:54.287 --> 15:56.890
YOU BEAT HIS ASS.

15:56.890 --> 15:59.526
YOU PROTECTED ME.

15:59.526 --> 16:03.203
YOU FOUGHT FOR ME.

16:06.039 --> 16:08.509
NOW I'M FIGHTING FOR YOU.

16:11.645 --> 16:15.081
BUT I NEED YOU TO FIGHT, TOO.

16:18.451 --> 16:20.721
YOU CAN'T GO.

16:20.721 --> 16:22.789
YOU CAN'T.

16:22.789 --> 16:24.357
[ SNIFFLES ]

16:24.357 --> 16:28.929
YOU CAN'T LEAVE
ME AND MAMA HERE.

16:28.929 --> 16:32.232
WE WOULD KILL EACH OTHER.

16:37.804 --> 16:40.440
YOU CAN'T DIE, BENNY.

16:45.612 --> 16:48.081
NOW...

16:48.081 --> 16:52.619
I'M GONNA FIGHT
TO GET YOU OUT OF HERE,

16:52.619 --> 16:57.357
BUT YOU HAVE TO FIGHT

16:57.357 --> 17:01.267
TO GET BETTER, "B."

17:01.267 --> 17:04.505
WE ARE FIGHTERS.

17:04.505 --> 17:09.910
WE FIGHT, AND WE WIN.

17:09.910 --> 17:12.713
WE WIN, BENNY.

17:12.713 --> 17:16.082
YOU DO NOT HAVE MY PERMISSION
TO LEAVE YET.

17:18.418 --> 17:21.154
THAT'S IT.

17:21.154 --> 17:24.057
THAT'S IT.

17:24.057 --> 17:27.594
I GOT NOTHING ELSE
TO SAY ABOUT IT.

17:27.594 --> 17:29.863
[ SNIFFLES ]

17:40.774 --> 17:43.510
WELL, LOOK WHO DECIDED
TO SHOW FOR WORK.

17:43.510 --> 17:45.411
HEY,
WHERE HAVE YOU BEEN?

17:45.411 --> 17:48.181
I'M NOT IN THE MOOD FOR YOU
THIS MORNING.

17:48.181 --> 17:49.516
OOH, THAT'S A FEISTY ATTITUDE
TO HAVE,

17:49.516 --> 17:51.217
CONSIDERING YOU HAVEN'T BEEN
AT WORK FOR FOUR DAYS.

17:51.217 --> 17:52.318
SHUT UP!

17:52.318 --> 17:53.654
JUST SHUT YOUR MOUTH.

17:53.654 --> 17:55.856
YOU UNDERSTAND ME, DEMON?
SHUT UP.

17:55.856 --> 17:57.791
WHO DO YOU THINK
YOU'RE TALKING TO?

17:57.791 --> 18:00.260
TRY ME THIS MORNING, CELINE.
PLEASE, TRY ME.

18:00.260 --> 18:02.035
WHAT? HANNA, I'M RIGHT HERE.
WHAT?

18:02.035 --> 18:03.770
DON'T MAKE ME BEAT YOUR ASS,
CELINE.

18:03.770 --> 18:05.806
OH, I'M SO SCARED.

18:05.806 --> 18:07.273
WATCH THAT LANGUAGE.
STOP IT!

18:07.273 --> 18:09.142
YOU DON'T EVEN KNOW WHAT
THE HELL YOU'RE TALKING ABOUT.

18:09.142 --> 18:10.143
JUST STOP.

18:10.143 --> 18:11.344
YOU ARE NOT MY BOSS!

18:11.344 --> 18:12.646
YOU GOT THAT RIGHT,

18:12.646 --> 18:13.947
'CAUSE YOUR ASS WOULD HAVE BEEN
FIRED MONTHS AGO.

18:13.947 --> 18:15.215
AND THAT KILLS YOU,
DOESN'T IT?

18:15.215 --> 18:17.784
THAT YOU CAN'T FIRE ME.
WELL, YOU CAN'T!

18:17.784 --> 18:19.653
YOU THINK JIM'S
GONNA KEEP YOU HERE?

18:19.653 --> 18:22.756
OH, I KNOW HE CAN.
HE DOES.

18:22.756 --> 18:24.157
DON'T SAY NOTHING ELSE
TO ME.

18:24.157 --> 18:25.959
YOU WOULDN'T EVEN GIVE HER
MY MESSAGES!

18:25.959 --> 18:27.360
DON'T SAY NOTHING ELSE
TO ME!

18:27.360 --> 18:29.696
JUST DO YOUR DAMN JOB,
AND STAY THE HELL AWAY FROM ME.

18:29.696 --> 18:32.432
GET OFF ME!

18:32.432 --> 18:35.135
OH.
YOU'RE OUT YOUR DAMN MIND!

18:35.135 --> 18:36.603
ARE YOU CRAZY?

18:36.603 --> 18:38.839
GET OFF ME.
GET OFF ME, HANNA.

18:38.839 --> 18:40.907
HEY, HEY, HEY, HEY.

18:40.907 --> 18:43.309
WHAT ARE YOU TWO DOING?

18:43.309 --> 18:44.410
TALKING.

18:44.410 --> 18:46.279
ACTIVELY TALKING.

18:46.279 --> 18:51.051
I DIDN'T EXPECT THIS KIND
OF BEHAVIOR FROM YOU, HANNA.

18:51.051 --> 18:53.019
I'M SORRY, MR. CRYER.

18:53.019 --> 18:55.522
GO HOME, CELINE.

18:55.522 --> 18:56.957
I'M NOT DONE, SIR.

18:56.957 --> 18:58.091
GO HOME.

18:58.091 --> 18:59.826
TAKE THE REST OF THE DAY OFF
TO COOL OFF.

18:59.826 --> 19:02.268
GO HOME.

19:02.268 --> 19:05.572
GREAT. JUST GREAT.

19:08.675 --> 19:10.376
I'M SORRY, MR. CRYER.

19:10.376 --> 19:13.413
I JUST CAME IN
TO TALK TO MRS. CRYER.

19:13.413 --> 19:14.548
IS SHE HERE?

19:14.548 --> 19:15.882
YES.

19:15.882 --> 19:17.283
HOW'S YOUR SON?

19:17.283 --> 19:19.653
NOT GOOD.

19:19.653 --> 19:21.788
I'M SORRY.

19:21.788 --> 19:23.624
THANK YOU.

19:23.624 --> 19:24.825
YEAH.

19:24.825 --> 19:25.959
WAIT.

19:25.959 --> 19:28.128
BEFORE YOU TALK
TO KATHERYN,

19:28.128 --> 19:30.263
I WANT TO TALK TO YOU
FOR A MINUTE.

19:30.263 --> 19:31.264
SIT DOWN.

19:31.264 --> 19:32.933
THAT WAS ROUGH.
GO ON. SIT DOWN.

19:35.035 --> 19:36.870
I'M FINE STANDING.

19:40.574 --> 19:43.710
LAST WEEK WHEN WYATT CAME HOME
LATE, DO YOU REMEMBER THAT?

19:43.710 --> 19:46.079
YES, I DO.

19:46.079 --> 19:47.914
YOU'RE AWARE THAT MY SON HAS
A SUBSTANCE‐ABUSE PROBLEM.

19:47.914 --> 19:49.182
YES.

19:49.182 --> 19:51.317
WELL, SADLY, THAT NIGHT,
HE'D BEEN USING.

19:51.317 --> 19:53.587
YES, I KNOW.

19:53.587 --> 19:55.622
WHEN HE GOT HERE,
HE SAID A FEW...

19:55.622 --> 19:57.490
WELL,
HE SAID A LOT OF THINGS.

19:57.490 --> 19:58.992
MM‐HMM.

19:58.992 --> 20:01.868
AND NONE OF THOSE THINGS MADE
ANY SENSE TO KATHERYN OR TO ME,

20:01.868 --> 20:04.337
AND I WAS WONDERING IF THEY MADE
ANY SENSE TO YOU.

20:04.337 --> 20:06.272
WHICH PART?

20:06.272 --> 20:08.975
ANYTHING HE SAID.

20:08.975 --> 20:12.312
IT MADE
A LOT OF SENSE TO ME.

20:12.312 --> 20:14.815
REALLY?

20:14.815 --> 20:18.218
WHICH PART WOULD THAT BE,
HANNA?

20:18.218 --> 20:21.688
EVERYTHING HE SAID.

20:21.688 --> 20:24.090
HMM.

20:24.090 --> 20:27.728
WHAT IS IT
YOU THINK HE SAID?

20:27.728 --> 20:32.298
THAT HE HAD HIT SOMEONE.

20:32.298 --> 20:34.768
REALLY?

20:34.768 --> 20:37.103
BECAUSE I DON'T REMEMBER
HEARING HIM SAY THAT.

20:39.706 --> 20:41.575
I DON'T KNOW WHY.

20:41.575 --> 20:44.811
YOU WERE STANDING
RIGHT HERE.

20:44.811 --> 20:48.849
BUT I SURE AS HELL DIDN'T HEAR
HIM SAY ANYTHING LIKE THAT.

20:48.849 --> 20:51.384
OKAY.

20:51.384 --> 20:54.588
CAN I TALK
TO MRS. CRYER, PLEASE?

20:54.588 --> 20:55.989
JUST A MOMENT.

20:55.989 --> 20:58.992
MR. CRYER,
WITH ALL DUE RESPECT,

20:58.992 --> 21:01.802
MY BABY IS ON LIFE SUPPORT,
AND I CAN'T DO THIS RIGHT NOW.

21:01.802 --> 21:03.604
I UNDERSTAND YOU'RE
GOING THROUGH A LOT.

21:03.604 --> 21:04.838
HANNA, I REALLY DO.

21:04.838 --> 21:06.940
SO, WHY DON'T YOU ALLOW ME
TO CUT TO THE CHASE.

21:06.940 --> 21:08.942
I DON'T KNOW WHAT IT IS
YOU THINK YOU HEARD.

21:08.942 --> 21:11.277
IT'S NOT WHAT I THINK.
IT'S WHAT I KNOW.

21:11.277 --> 21:13.346
WHAT DO YOU THINK YOU KNOW,
HANNA?

21:13.346 --> 21:16.149
MR. CRYER, I HEARD HIM SAY
THAT HE HAD HIT SOMEONE

21:16.149 --> 21:18.118
AND THAT HE THOUGHT
HE WAS DEAD.

21:18.118 --> 21:19.119
YEAH.

21:19.119 --> 21:21.387
YOU SEE ‐‐ WYATT!

21:23.890 --> 21:26.426
Wyatt: YEAH?
COME ON IN HERE, SON.

21:26.426 --> 21:29.830
SEE, I ASKED WYATT
IF HE'D SAID ANYTHING

21:29.830 --> 21:32.666
ABOUT HITTING ANYBODY AND
THINKING THAT THEY WERE DEAD,

21:32.666 --> 21:34.100
AND HE SAID THAT HE DIDN'T.

21:34.100 --> 21:35.569
HE DIDN'T SAY THAT.

21:35.569 --> 21:36.870
THAT RIGHT, SON?

21:40.106 --> 21:42.776
YEAH.

21:42.776 --> 21:45.045
I CAN'T REMEMBER
WHAT I SAID.

21:47.313 --> 21:50.116
BUT YOU DIDN'T SAY
THAT YOU HAD HIT SOMEONE

21:50.116 --> 21:52.252
AND YOU THOUGHT
THEY WERE DEAD.

21:52.252 --> 21:54.387
NO.

21:54.387 --> 21:56.322
NO.

21:56.322 --> 21:58.859
WELL, THERE YOU HAVE IT.

22:02.268 --> 22:04.905
OKAY.

22:06.673 --> 22:09.309
CAN I TALK TO MRS. CRYER NOW,
PLEASE?

22:09.309 --> 22:12.412
MRS. CRYER IS VERY BUSY, HANNA,
BUT I TELL YOU WHAT I'LL DO.

22:12.412 --> 22:15.616
I WILL TELL MRS. CRYER THAT YOU
NEEDED TO TAKE SOME TIME OFF.

22:18.118 --> 22:20.420
YOU TAKE
AS MUCH AS YOU WANT.

22:27.628 --> 22:29.996
OKAY.

22:32.599 --> 22:34.100
WHY DON'T YOU GRAB
YOUR PURSE?

22:34.100 --> 22:37.337
AND, FOR THE SAKE OF PEACE,
USE THE FRONT DOOR.

22:41.508 --> 22:44.277
WOULDN'T WANT ANYTHING
HAPPENING TO YOU.

22:58.592 --> 23:00.934
JIM, DID I HEAR HANNA?

23:00.934 --> 23:02.703
NO.

23:04.871 --> 23:06.607
JIM.

23:06.607 --> 23:09.075
YES, HANNA WAS HERE.

23:09.075 --> 23:10.276
I NEED TO TALK TO HER.

23:10.276 --> 23:12.579
NO, YOU DON'T NEED
TO TALK TO HER.

23:13.479 --> 23:15.516
WATCH ME.

23:16.950 --> 23:21.688
YOU KNOW THIS IS BAD,
KATHERYN.

23:32.566 --> 23:34.868
HANNA.

23:36.703 --> 23:38.071
MRS. CRYER.

23:38.071 --> 23:41.742
I'M SO SORRY.

23:41.742 --> 23:45.612
I'M SORRY, TOO.

23:45.612 --> 23:47.714
WHERE ARE YOU GOING?

23:47.714 --> 23:49.883
BACK TO THE HOSPITAL.

23:49.883 --> 23:51.384
LET ME GET MY KEYS.
I'LL TAKE YOU.

23:51.384 --> 23:52.953
NO.

23:52.953 --> 23:55.121
NO?

23:55.121 --> 23:57.090
HANNA, I'LL TAKE YOU.

23:57.090 --> 23:59.560
NO, THANK YOU.

23:59.560 --> 24:02.035
I'LL CALL YOU.

24:07.073 --> 24:09.442
HANNA.

24:12.746 --> 24:14.014
WHAT DID SHE SAY?

24:14.014 --> 24:15.315
I'M GOING
TO THE HOSPITAL.

24:15.315 --> 24:17.584
NO, YOU ARE STAYING HERE.
I NEED YOU TO STAY IN THE HOUSE.

24:17.584 --> 24:19.152
JIM.
KATHERYN.

24:19.152 --> 24:22.055
I SAID I AM GOING
TO THE HOSPITAL.

24:22.055 --> 24:23.857
AND I SAID YOU ARE NOT GOING
TO THE HOSPITAL.

24:23.857 --> 24:25.125
YOU'RE STAYING
IN THIS HOUSE.

24:25.125 --> 24:27.828
WATCH ME.

24:27.828 --> 24:31.464
KATHERYN CRYER!

24:44.945 --> 24:46.613
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]
YEAH.

24:46.613 --> 24:49.282
CANDACE.

24:49.282 --> 24:51.484
HI.

24:51.484 --> 24:53.486
HI.

24:53.486 --> 24:54.755
YOU GOT IN LATE.

24:54.755 --> 24:57.023
YEAH.

24:57.023 --> 24:58.592
HOW'S YOUR BROTHER?

24:58.592 --> 25:01.735
NOT WELL.

25:01.735 --> 25:03.504
I'M SORRY.

25:03.504 --> 25:07.373
AMANDA,
WE NEED TO TALK.

25:07.373 --> 25:08.575
OKAY.

25:10.376 --> 25:11.411
OH, OKAY.

25:11.411 --> 25:13.980
ALL RIGHT,
I'LL LET YOU GUYS TALK.

25:13.980 --> 25:16.717
JEFFERY'S SEEING HIS MOM
TOMORROW.

25:16.717 --> 25:18.785
YOU'RE SEEING
YOUR MOTHER?

25:18.785 --> 25:20.253
YEAH.

25:20.253 --> 25:22.455
WELL, FIRST, I'M GONNA GO TO
THE STORE AND BUY SOME CLOTHES,

25:22.455 --> 25:24.390
AND THEN I'M GONNA MEET WITH HER
FOR LUNCH TOMORROW.

25:24.390 --> 25:26.059
HMM.

25:26.059 --> 25:28.328
ALL RIGHT, WELL, YOU GUYS TALK.
I'M GONNA GO AND HIT THE SHOWER.

25:28.328 --> 25:30.931
AND, PLEASE, GET THE WATER UP,
AND DRY THE MIRROR OFF, JEFFERY.

25:30.931 --> 25:32.465
YOU DON'T HAVE A MAID
AROUND HERE.

25:32.465 --> 25:34.601
SURE.

25:34.601 --> 25:37.738
THANK YOU FOR
THAT HELPFUL INFORMATION.

25:39.673 --> 25:40.841
LOOK AT YOU.

25:40.841 --> 25:42.308
WHAT?

25:42.308 --> 25:43.977
MAKING DEMANDS.

25:43.977 --> 25:46.146
I KNOW, RIGHT?

25:48.081 --> 25:50.851
HAVE YOUR PARENTS CALLED YOU
ABOUT YOUR INHERITANCE?

25:50.851 --> 25:53.520
NO.
I HAVEN'T HEARD FROM THEM.

25:53.520 --> 25:55.756
OKAY.

25:55.756 --> 25:59.593
TODAY, WE SHOULD ACTUALLY GO
AND FILE THE LAWSUIT.

25:59.593 --> 26:01.301
NO MORE WASTING TIME.

26:01.301 --> 26:02.703
OKAY. LET'S DO IT.

26:02.703 --> 26:05.338
I WANT TO GET THE TUITION
PAID OFF AT THE DESIGN SCHOOL.

26:05.338 --> 26:06.907
OKAY. GOOD.

26:06.907 --> 26:08.642
I'M GONNA GET DRESSED,

26:08.642 --> 26:11.444
AND WE SHOULD
GET THIS THING GOING.

26:11.444 --> 26:13.246
OKAY.

26:13.246 --> 26:15.015
I WILL, TOO.

26:19.019 --> 26:21.121
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

26:21.121 --> 26:23.524
[ Woman over P. A. ]
<i>PAGING DR. STATEMAN.</i>

26:23.524 --> 26:25.659
<i>DR. STATEMAN, PLEASE.</i>

26:25.659 --> 26:27.961
[ TELEPHONE RINGING ]

26:33.133 --> 26:35.602
<i>ORTHO TECH TO PEDIATRICS.</i>

26:35.602 --> 26:37.771
<i>ORTHO TECH TO PEDIATRICS.</i>

26:42.342 --> 26:44.210
<i>SECURITY TO ADMITTING.</i>

26:44.210 --> 26:46.146
<i>SECURITY TO ADMITTING.</i>

26:52.586 --> 26:55.455
Katheryn: HANNA.

26:58.091 --> 27:00.561
MRS. CRYER?

27:00.561 --> 27:04.037
YOU BEAT ME HERE.

27:06.507 --> 27:09.342
HOW ARE YOU?

27:09.342 --> 27:12.879
I'M OKAY.

27:12.879 --> 27:15.381
I'M SORRY.

27:15.381 --> 27:17.183
I HAD TO COME.

27:17.183 --> 27:20.320
HOW'S HE DOING?

27:20.320 --> 27:22.556
I'M WAITING TO SEE HIM.

27:22.556 --> 27:26.126
VISITING HOURS
ARE IN A FEW MINUTES.

27:26.126 --> 27:28.128
[ SIGHS ]

27:28.128 --> 27:29.963
WHAT ARE
THE DOCTORS SAYING?

27:29.963 --> 27:33.266
WELL, THEY'RE TELLING ME
THAT HE'S BRAIN‐DEAD.

27:33.266 --> 27:37.170
THEY'RE SAYING THAT I SHOULD
TAKE HIM OFF OF LIFE SUPPORT.

27:42.676 --> 27:44.878
CAN I SPEAK TO THE DOCTOR?

27:44.878 --> 27:47.480
OKAY?

27:47.480 --> 27:49.783
PLEASE?
WHAT'S HIS NAME?

27:49.783 --> 27:51.552
WHICH ONE?

27:51.552 --> 27:53.119
HE HAS A FEW DOCTORS.

27:53.119 --> 27:54.788
BUT WHO IS THE PRIMARY?

27:54.788 --> 27:56.590
HE DOESN'T HAVE ONE.

27:56.590 --> 27:58.124
I DON'T UNDERSTAND.

27:58.124 --> 28:00.627
THERE IS NO ONE DOCTOR
FOR HIM.

28:00.627 --> 28:04.605
THERE'S ONLY A FEW DOCTORS,
AND THEY'RE HERE FOR EVERYBODY.

28:04.605 --> 28:06.072
HANNA, I'M CONFUSED.

28:06.072 --> 28:07.641
WHO IS TREATING BENNY?

28:07.641 --> 28:09.610
THEY ALL ARE.

28:09.610 --> 28:10.911
WHAT?

28:10.911 --> 28:12.546
MRS. CRYER,
THAT'S THE WAY IT IS

28:12.546 --> 28:14.380
WHEN YOU DON'T HAVE
HEALTH INSURANCE.

28:16.917 --> 28:19.986
WELL,
CAN I SPEAK TO THE NURSE?

28:19.986 --> 28:21.121
[ SCOFFS ]

28:21.121 --> 28:23.156
YEAH, YOU DON'T WANT TO TALK
TO THESE PEOPLE.

28:23.156 --> 28:25.458
PLEASE?

28:28.394 --> 28:30.363
ALL RIGHT.

28:30.363 --> 28:31.832
GO ON.

28:34.601 --> 28:36.202
EXCUSE ME.

28:36.202 --> 28:38.505
EXCUSE ME.

28:38.505 --> 28:41.374
YES?

28:41.374 --> 28:43.476
CAN YOU PAGE BENJAMIN YOUNG'S
DOCTOR, PLEASE?

28:43.476 --> 28:45.378
WE'D LIKE TO HAVE
A CONFERENCE WITH HIM.

28:45.378 --> 28:48.114
I'M SORRY. SAY WHAT?

28:48.114 --> 28:52.385
HIS MOTHER AND I WOULD LIKE
TO MEET WITH HIM.

28:52.385 --> 28:54.855
THERE'S NO DOCTOR HERE
RIGHT NOW.

28:54.855 --> 28:56.489
THERE ISN'T?

28:56.489 --> 28:58.024
NO.

28:58.024 --> 29:00.060
WELL, WHAT WOULD YOU DO
IN CASE OF AN EMERGENCY?

29:00.060 --> 29:02.135
THE RESIDENTS ARE HERE.

29:02.135 --> 29:04.237
RESIDENTS?
YES.

29:04.237 --> 29:05.806
WOULD YOU LIKE TO SPEAK
TO ONE OF THEM?

29:05.806 --> 29:08.441
NO. HANNA.

29:08.441 --> 29:10.243
IS THIS
HOW YOU HAVE BEEN TREATED

29:10.243 --> 29:11.512
SINCE YOU HAVE BEEN HERE?

29:11.512 --> 29:12.646
WHAT ELSE CAN I DO?

29:12.646 --> 29:14.080
YOU COULD HAVE COME TO ME.

29:14.080 --> 29:16.817
MY FATHER'S NAME
IS ON A WING HERE.

29:16.817 --> 29:18.819
NO, I COULDN'T.

29:18.819 --> 29:21.622
HANNA,
YOU HELPED ME THROUGH CANCER.

29:21.622 --> 29:25.158
I AM NOT ABOUT TO LET YOU
GO THROUGH THIS ALONE.

29:25.158 --> 29:27.427
MRS. CRYER,
I CAN HANDLE THIS.

29:27.427 --> 29:29.362
NO, YOU CAN'T.

29:29.362 --> 29:31.998
HE NEEDS TO BE MOVED.

29:31.998 --> 29:33.867
I DON'T THINK
THAT'S A GOOD IDEA.

29:33.867 --> 29:35.602
AND WHY NOT?

29:35.602 --> 29:39.072
HE'S FINE HERE.

29:39.072 --> 29:44.778
HANNA, HE IS NOT GETTING
THE BEST CARE HERE.

29:44.778 --> 29:47.581
HE NEEDS TO BE MOVED.

29:47.581 --> 29:50.016
I HAVE TO LET HIM
STAY HERE.

29:50.016 --> 29:53.086
WHY?

29:53.086 --> 29:56.222
CAN YOU JUST GO, PLEASE?

29:58.124 --> 30:00.594
I'M SORRY.

30:00.594 --> 30:01.702
HANNA ‐‐
CAN YOU...

30:01.702 --> 30:05.138
I'LL CALL YOU, OKAY?

30:06.907 --> 30:08.875
I'LL CALL YOU.

30:31.865 --> 30:33.333
HEY.

30:33.333 --> 30:35.168
HEY.

30:42.008 --> 30:45.712
SO, HOW ARE YOU,
REALLY?

30:45.712 --> 30:49.215
NOT GOOD.

30:49.215 --> 30:52.619
MY BROTHER
IS ON LIFE SUPPORT.

30:52.619 --> 30:54.888
CANDACE, I'M SO SORRY.

30:58.291 --> 31:03.303
I'M JUST SO MAD.

31:03.303 --> 31:06.773
THIS IS SO UNFAIR.

31:06.773 --> 31:09.042
IT'S GONNA BE OKAY.

31:09.042 --> 31:13.379
I'M TIRED
OF THESE RICH PEOPLE

31:13.379 --> 31:15.882
TURNING THEIR NOSES UP AT ME.

31:15.882 --> 31:19.085
THESE ‐‐
THESE PUBLIC HOSPITALS.

31:19.085 --> 31:23.423
THEY WON'T HELP ME.

31:23.423 --> 31:25.491
CANDACE,
WHO ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?

31:25.491 --> 31:28.729
JIM CRYER.

31:31.598 --> 31:33.266
WHAT DID HE DO?

31:33.266 --> 31:36.402
HE WON'T HELP ME.

31:36.402 --> 31:38.138
SO, WHAT ARE YOU
GONNA DO?

31:38.138 --> 31:40.841
EVERYTHING I CAN
TO BRING HIM DOWN.

31:40.841 --> 31:43.510
YOU KNOW IF YOU BRING HIM DOWN,
MY FATHER IS HIS RUNNING MATE.

31:43.510 --> 31:45.411
AND?

31:45.411 --> 31:47.313
AND HE DOESN'T
DESERVE THAT.

31:47.313 --> 31:50.016
YOU GET CLOSE TO FIRE,
YOU BURN.

31:50.016 --> 31:51.985
NO, NO, NO.
HE'S A GOOD GUY.

31:51.985 --> 31:53.654
WHO DIDN'T STAND UP
TO YOUR MOTHER.

31:53.654 --> 31:55.656
YES, HE DID.

31:55.656 --> 31:59.192
DON'T YOU WANT TO GET BACK
AT YOUR MOTHER?

31:59.192 --> 32:01.234
I LOVE MY MOTHER.

32:01.234 --> 32:03.436
DON'T YOU WANT
TO GET BACK AT HER

32:03.436 --> 32:06.907
FOR THE THINGS SHE SAID TO YOU
AND THE WAY SHE TREATS YOU?

32:06.907 --> 32:09.976
SHE'S MY MOM.

32:09.976 --> 32:12.846
SO?

32:12.846 --> 32:16.550
SHE HATES THAT YOU'RE GAY.

32:16.550 --> 32:18.785
CANDACE ‐‐

32:18.785 --> 32:21.855
SO, YOU'RE JUST GONNA
GO BUY A NICE SUIT,

32:21.855 --> 32:25.792
GET DRESSED,
AND GO SEE HER?

32:25.792 --> 32:28.128
YEAH.

32:28.128 --> 32:30.463
WHY?

32:30.463 --> 32:32.365
BECAUSE I KNOW
SHE WANTS TO MEET ME,

32:32.365 --> 32:34.768
AND I KNOW SHE EXPECTS TO SEE ME
A CERTAIN WAY.

32:34.768 --> 32:35.869
THEN DO THE OPPOSITE.

32:35.869 --> 32:39.172
LET HER KNOW
SHE CAN'T CONTROL YOU.

32:39.172 --> 32:41.207
CANDACE,
THIS ISN'T MY FIGHT.

32:41.207 --> 32:43.309
JEFFERY,
WHAT DOES THAT MEAN?

32:43.309 --> 32:44.845
YOU'RE MAD AT MR. ‐‐

32:47.681 --> 32:49.182
YOU'RE MAD AT MR. CRYER.

32:49.182 --> 32:52.285
AND YOU'RE MAD
AT YOUR MOTHER.

32:52.285 --> 32:53.419
ADMIT IT.

32:53.419 --> 32:55.221
CANDACE ‐‐

32:55.221 --> 32:58.659
HAVE YOU SEEN
HOW FREE AMANDA IS?

32:58.659 --> 33:01.034
SHE'S SPEAKING HER MIND.

33:01.034 --> 33:04.404
SHE'S ‐‐
SHE'S A DIFFERENT GIRL.

33:04.404 --> 33:06.006
SHE'S FALLING APART.

33:06.006 --> 33:07.841
NO, SHE'S NOT.
TRUST ME. SHE IS.

33:07.841 --> 33:08.909
STAY ON TRACK.

33:11.011 --> 33:13.079
LET ME GO WITH YOU
TO MEET YOUR MOTHER.

33:13.079 --> 33:14.548
WHY?

33:14.548 --> 33:17.884
WE CAN REALLY SHAKE HER UP.

33:17.884 --> 33:20.921
NO, NO, NO, NO, NO.

33:20.921 --> 33:23.189
YES. TRUST ME, JEFFERY.

33:23.189 --> 33:25.892
NO, NO, NO, NO. I'M NOT GONNA
LET YOU DESTROY MY PARENTS.

33:25.892 --> 33:28.962
I'M AFTER JIM.

33:28.962 --> 33:33.099
THEN WHY DO YOU WANT
TO MEET WITH MY MOTHER?

33:33.099 --> 33:36.069
TO HELP YOU.

33:43.577 --> 33:45.712
[ SIRENS WAILING ]

33:47.280 --> 33:49.983
[ Woman over P. A ]
<i>PLEASE DIAL 884.</i>

33:49.983 --> 33:52.953
<i>DR. BRONNAN, PLEASE DIAL 884.</i>

33:55.722 --> 33:57.257
HI.

33:57.257 --> 34:00.193
HEY, MICHAEL.

34:00.193 --> 34:03.203
HOW IS HE?

34:03.203 --> 34:06.239
NO CHANGE.

34:06.239 --> 34:09.209
I'M SORRY.

34:09.209 --> 34:11.077
OH.

34:11.077 --> 34:13.780
I BROUGHT SOME FOOD
FOR YOU.

34:13.780 --> 34:16.282
I KNOW
YOU HAVEN'T EATEN.

34:16.282 --> 34:19.586
I ACTUALLY ATE BREAKFAST
THIS MORNING.

34:19.586 --> 34:20.754
THAT'S GOOD.

34:20.754 --> 34:22.155
EATING IS GOOD.

34:22.155 --> 34:24.958
YOU CAME ALL THE WAY DOWN HERE
TO BRING ME SOME FOOD?

34:24.958 --> 34:27.260
YEAH.

34:27.260 --> 34:29.963
THAT'S ALL?

34:29.963 --> 34:31.732
YEAH.

34:33.967 --> 34:36.637
WELL, NO.

34:36.637 --> 34:38.304
WHAT IS IT?

34:38.304 --> 34:41.307
IT'S SO QUIET AT THE HOUSE
WITHOUT MY GRANDDAUGHTER.

34:41.307 --> 34:43.443
HMM.

34:43.443 --> 34:44.845
I DON'T KNOW
HOW MANY MORE TIMES

34:44.845 --> 34:48.515
I'M GONNA BE ABLE TO CUT
MY GRASS AND YOURS.

34:48.515 --> 34:50.984
CUT MY GRASS?

34:50.984 --> 34:53.453
YEAH.

34:53.453 --> 34:55.321
YOU CUT MY GRASS?

34:55.321 --> 34:56.757
YESTERDAY.

34:56.757 --> 34:59.192
OH, MICHAEL, I WISH YOU WOULDN'T
HAVE DONE THAT.

34:59.192 --> 35:00.293
OH, I'M SORRY.

35:00.293 --> 35:02.168
IT'S JUST THE GRASS
WAS GETTING HIGH.

35:02.168 --> 35:04.805
I DIDN'T WANT ANYBODY TO THINK
THAT NO ONE LIVED THERE.

35:04.805 --> 35:08.274
BENNY CUTS THE GRASS.

35:08.274 --> 35:09.409
OH.

35:09.409 --> 35:11.177
AND HE'S SO PROUD OF IT.

35:11.177 --> 35:12.979
I KNOW.
I'M SO SORRY.

35:12.979 --> 35:14.147
I DIDN'T KNOW.

35:14.147 --> 35:16.082
IT'S OKAY.

35:16.082 --> 35:19.820
I NOTICED IT LAST NIGHT.

35:19.820 --> 35:22.288
HE'S THE ONE
THAT'S GONNA BE MAD AT YOU.

35:22.288 --> 35:26.292
I'LL TAKE THAT.

35:26.292 --> 35:28.061
AND YOU CUT IT WRONG.

35:28.061 --> 35:30.296
[ CHUCKLES ]

35:30.296 --> 35:31.497
HE USED TO SAY, "MAMA,

35:31.497 --> 35:33.834
IT'S GOT TO COME FROM THE HOUSE
TO THE STREET."

35:33.834 --> 35:35.602
OH.

35:40.173 --> 35:44.044
BEEN CUTTING THE GRASS
SINCE HE WAS A LITTLE BOY.

35:44.044 --> 35:47.180
IT WAS HIS FIRST JOB.

35:47.180 --> 35:49.149
[ CHUCKLES ]

35:52.853 --> 35:55.589
I DON'T MEAN TO BE MEAN TO YOU,
MICHAEL.

35:55.589 --> 35:58.058
I APPRECIATE YOU
CUTTING THE GRASS.

35:58.058 --> 35:59.059
OKAY.

35:59.059 --> 36:00.867
AND I APPRECIATE
THE FOOD.

36:00.867 --> 36:02.536
NO, NO, I GET IT.

36:02.536 --> 36:05.371
YOU WANT TO BE
WITH YOUR SON.

36:05.371 --> 36:07.340
YOU UNDERSTAND.

36:07.340 --> 36:08.809
OF COURSE.

36:08.809 --> 36:11.411
OKAY.

36:11.411 --> 36:13.446
I'LL TALK TO YOU LATER.

36:13.446 --> 36:15.181
OKAY.

36:16.883 --> 36:20.554
I WON'T CUT YOUR GRASS
ANYMORE.

36:20.554 --> 36:22.723
BYE.

36:26.627 --> 36:28.795
YOU HEAR THAT, BENNY?

36:28.795 --> 36:31.798
THAT MAN'S MESSING
WITH YOUR GRASS.

36:31.798 --> 36:34.901
YOU GOT TO GET ON UP
FROM HERE, NOW.

36:34.901 --> 36:36.937
COME ON NOW, BABY.

36:36.937 --> 36:39.072
COME ON. COME BACK.

36:41.542 --> 36:43.810
COME BACK, BABY.

36:53.286 --> 36:56.557
[ SIGHS ]

37:16.850 --> 37:18.985
[ SIGHS ]

37:29.029 --> 37:31.131
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

37:36.236 --> 37:37.771
KATHERYN.

37:37.771 --> 37:39.606
I DON'T WANT TO HEAR IT.

37:39.606 --> 37:40.974
SHOULDN'T HAVE GONE THERE.

37:40.974 --> 37:42.576
YOU DON'T UNDERSTAND.

37:42.576 --> 37:46.112
NO, YOU DON'T UNDERSTAND.

37:46.112 --> 37:48.649
I'M HAVING HIM MOVED
TO ANOTHER HOSPITAL.

37:48.649 --> 37:50.984
YOU'RE WHAT?

37:50.984 --> 37:52.318
YOU HEARD ME.
KATHERYN.

37:52.318 --> 37:54.154
THE CARE IS DEPLORABLE THERE,
JIM.

37:54.154 --> 37:56.456
THEY DON'T EVEN HAVE
FULL‐TIME DOCTORS.

37:56.456 --> 37:58.358
JUST RESIDENTS
WALKING AROUND.

37:58.358 --> 38:00.534
HE IS NOT BEING LOOKED AFTER
AT ALL.

38:00.534 --> 38:01.868
I DON'T CARE.

38:01.868 --> 38:04.237
YOU CANNOT HAVE HIM MOVED.

38:04.237 --> 38:06.339
IT'S NONE OF YOUR BUSINESS.

38:06.339 --> 38:08.341
NOW YOU SOUND LIKE HANNA.

38:08.341 --> 38:11.545
WHAT DID SHE SAY?

38:11.545 --> 38:13.013
SHE ASKED ME TO LEAVE.

38:13.013 --> 38:14.981
THAT'S BECAUSE SHE KNOWS
WYATT DID THIS.

38:14.981 --> 38:18.652
JIM, I HAVE TO HAVE THAT CHILD
MOVED, AND SHE WON'T LET ME.

38:18.652 --> 38:19.853
SHE'S HIS MOTHER.

38:19.853 --> 38:21.021
I KNOW THAT.

38:21.021 --> 38:22.623
I'M A MOTHER, JIM.

38:22.623 --> 38:24.691
WHY WON'T SHE LET ME
HELP HER?

38:24.691 --> 38:25.959
SHE DOESN'T TRUST YOU.

38:25.959 --> 38:28.595
THAT'S WHY SHE DOESN'T
WANT YOU TO MOVE HER SON.

38:28.595 --> 38:31.431
SHE THINKS YOU'RE TRYING TO BUY
HER SILENCE WITH KINDNESS.

38:31.431 --> 38:32.999
ONE OF THESE DAYS,
SHE'S GONNA SUE US,

38:32.999 --> 38:35.135
AND WYATT'S GONNA GO TO JAIL
FOR THE REST OF HIS LIFE.

38:35.135 --> 38:36.202
IT'S JUST A MATTER OF TIME.

38:36.202 --> 38:37.838
JIM ‐‐
KATHERYN.

38:37.838 --> 38:39.072
LET IT GO.

38:39.072 --> 38:42.408
LET IT GO,
AND LET ME HANDLE IT.

38:42.408 --> 38:46.379
FOR ONCE IN YOUR LIFE,
FOLLOW MY RULES.

39:14.748 --> 39:17.383
HI, BENNY.

39:17.383 --> 39:20.787
THE CLOCK IS TICKING.

39:20.787 --> 39:23.456
FOR WHAT?

39:23.456 --> 39:26.727
FOR YOU TO EITHER BRING ME
THAT BABY

39:26.727 --> 39:28.762
OR TELL ME WHERE HE IS.

39:28.762 --> 39:31.732
YOU JUST WORRY ABOUT
YOUR BABY, OKAY?

39:31.732 --> 39:33.767
MY BABY
IS IN GOD'S HANDS.

39:33.767 --> 39:37.804
AND YOU THINK MINE
IS IN THE DEVIL'S.

39:37.804 --> 39:41.542
YOUR HIS MOTHER.

39:43.176 --> 39:45.245
SEE, BENNY?

39:45.245 --> 39:48.381
YOU GOT TO WAKE UP.

39:59.593 --> 40:00.867
HANNA YOUNG.

40:00.867 --> 40:02.869
YES?

40:02.869 --> 40:05.171
HERE YOU GO.
WHAT'S THIS?

40:07.708 --> 40:09.743
OH, MY GOD!

40:09.743 --> 40:12.579
OH, MY GOD, TONY!

40:12.579 --> 40:14.147
I'M SORRY.

40:14.147 --> 40:15.782
YOU'RE REALLY
GONNA DO THIS TO HIM?!

40:15.782 --> 40:17.551
I'M SORRY, HANNA.

40:17.551 --> 40:19.786
YOU'RE TAKING ME TO COURT?!
YES.

40:19.786 --> 40:22.422
YOU KNOW GOOD DAMN WELL I DON'T
HAVE THE MONEY TO FIGHT THIS!

40:22.422 --> 40:23.857
LOOK,
THE BOY'S A VEGETABLE.

40:23.857 --> 40:25.626
I WANT HIM TAKEN OFF
OF LIFE SUPPORT.

40:25.626 --> 40:26.827
WHO THE HELL ARE YOU?

40:26.827 --> 40:27.994
HIS FATHER.

40:27.994 --> 40:29.262
WHO ARE YOU?

40:29.262 --> 40:31.898
YOU GONNA DO THIS
TO ME NOW?!

40:31.898 --> 40:34.434
YOU GONNA TAKE ME
TO COURT?!

40:34.434 --> 40:36.036
THAT'S YOUR SON
LAYING THERE!

40:36.036 --> 40:37.237
THAT'S YOUR SON!

40:37.237 --> 40:38.404
YOU GONNA TAKE ME TO COURT

40:38.404 --> 40:41.608
SO SOME JUDGE CAN TELL ME
TO TAKE HIS LIFE?!

40:41.608 --> 40:44.010
JUST LET HIM GO.

40:44.010 --> 40:46.179
HOW YOU GONNA EXPECT ME
TO LET HIM GO?!

40:46.179 --> 40:48.348
YOU WERE NEVER THERE!

40:48.348 --> 40:49.516
TOMORROW MORNING, HANNA.

40:49.516 --> 40:50.784
IT'S AN EMERGENCY HEARING.

40:50.784 --> 40:52.986
JUST LET HIM GO, HANNA.
TONY!

40:52.986 --> 40:54.555
LET HIM GO.
STOP!

40:56.022 --> 40:57.457
JUST STOP!

40:57.457 --> 40:59.425
YOU CAN'T TELL ME
TO LET HIM GO!

40:59.425 --> 41:01.034
YOU WEREN'T THERE.

41:01.034 --> 41:02.869
YOU WERE NEVER THERE.

41:02.869 --> 41:05.271
YOU NEVER HELD HIM.

41:05.271 --> 41:08.274
YOU DON'T KNOW NOTHING
ABOUT THAT BOY.

41:13.346 --> 41:14.681
HE WOULDN'T WANT TO BE
LIKE THAT.

41:14.681 --> 41:15.682
HOW CAN YOU DO THIS?

41:15.682 --> 41:17.017
YOU DON'T KNOW NOTHING
ABOUT HIM.

41:17.017 --> 41:19.085
YOU DON'T KNOW
NOTHING ABOUT HIM!

41:19.085 --> 41:21.187
YOU DON'T KNOW
NOTHING ABOUT HIM.

41:23.189 --> 41:28.061
TONY,
WHAT IS WRONG WITH YOU?

41:31.231 --> 41:33.800
<i>NEXT WEEK ON "THE HAVES</i>
<i>AND THE HAVE NOTS"...</i>

41:33.800 --> 41:35.368
WE'LL SEE
TOMORROW IN COURT.

41:35.368 --> 41:37.303
AIN'T NO JUDGE IN HELL
GONNA MAKE ME UNPLUG MY CHILD.

41:37.303 --> 41:38.972
YOUR HONOR, THIS IS WRONG.

41:38.972 --> 41:40.340
WHAT KIND OF GAY
ARE YOU?

41:40.340 --> 41:41.675
I DON'T KNOW
WHAT THAT MEANS.

41:41.675 --> 41:44.210
THIS IS JEFFERY.

41:44.210 --> 41:45.211
HI.

41:45.211 --> 41:46.547
TO YOUR NEW GOVERNOR.

41:46.547 --> 41:48.348
YES.

41:48.348 --> 41:50.416
TO A LYING, CHEATING...

41:50.416 --> 41:53.086
I'M REALLY TIRED
OF THIS LITTLE ‐‐

41:53.086 --> 41:54.521
...BEAST.

41:54.521 --> 41:56.757
DO YOU HAVE A GUN?

41:56.757 --> 41:58.158
NO.

41:58.158 --> 41:59.359
THEN WHAT'S THIS?
